Using the temperature of a single year does not suffice to test the warming effect, as in simulation models the result is largely influenced by the initial configuration of temperatures [25, 30, 32]. Thus, we extrapolated the temperatures for Year 2 and 3 based on the temperature in Year 1, indicated by T
j(k) (k = 1…3, j = 1…365) (Fig. 1c). The daily accumulative precipitation (PP
j) and daily photoperiod (SD
j) on the jth day of the year as required model parameters were processed in the same manner, as shown in Eqs. (3) and (4).3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
